  "name": "Bollinger DMI Breakout Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies trading opportunities by detecting breakouts from a Bollinger Bands squeeze while confirming trend direction with the Directional Movement Index (DMI). It operates on 15-minute bars, utilizing a 20-period simple moving average for the Bollinger Bands and focusing on significant price movements.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TechnicalPattern trading algorithm in Python that identifies and trades on the simultaneous occurrence of a breakout from a Bollinger Bands squeeze combined with a confirmed Directional Movement Index (DMI) trend signal on 15-minute bars. Use Bollinger Bands set to a 20-period simple moving average with band widths below the 10th percentile over the past 50 bars to detect low volatility squeeze. Confirm breakout entry only when price closes above the upper band (for long) or below the lower band (for short) and the +DI line crosses above the \u2013DI line with an Average Directional Index (ADX) above 25, indicating a strong trend. Exit positions when the price closes inside the bands or when ADX drops below 20. Incorporate volume confirmation by requiring On Balance Volume (OBV) to be trending upwards (positive slope) for long entries and downwards (negative slope) for short entries, calculated over the previous 10 bars. Provide clear entry and exit signals with stop-loss set at the opposite Bollinger Band edge.",
